	<chapter id="ch1">
		<page id="pageIntro">
			<p underline="true" bold="true" align="center" space="20">Introduction</p>
			<p space="10">In my study of the Art, I have encountered countless Pages, each with a unique combination of Symbols. I have copied and used these Pages in my Descriptive Books to Link to amazing new Ages, but their true meanings have long eluded me.</p>
			<p space="10">In ancient D'ni, the D'ni people would have written their Descriptive and Linking Books in their special language, but the Pages I have collected are not written like that.</p>
			<p>After many years of study, I have discovered that the Pages are written in Narayani, the language of the people of the Age of Narayan. I will share with you what I have learned about Pages and the Narayani written on them.</p>
		</page>
